messages.text:
Preview bug is fixed. The uploader was forcing a square crop box and then applying a landscape aspect correction on top, which double-transformed portrait images — that's why foreheads.

```css
.upload-preview img {
  object-fit: cover;
  aspect-ratio: 1 / 1;
}
```

I also made the preview render immediately from the local file instead of waiting for the upload round-trip, so it feels instant now. Sign-in options stay parked per your call — I've added a stub entry to the launch decisions doc with the four candidate approaches and the open questions, so when we pick this up we're not reconstructing the whole conversation from memory. The form already looks noticeably less like a tax return.
